22:14 am)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> A no brainer...</span><hr size=1> All these high level guilds are complaining how CH was nerfed to all shit and the cleric gets the shit kicked out of him/her, here.. let my n00bie self give a way to help solve this.<br>
<br>
a_cleric01 says, &quot;Casting Complete Heal on a_tank01.&quot;<br>
an instant later if the magician is on the ball,<br>
a_magician says, &quot;Casting Call of the Hero on a_cleric01.&quot;<br>
<br>
Hrmm, both 10 second casting time and the cleric get's Call of the Hero cast on him about a second after she/he complete heals the tank.  <br>
<br>
/shrug<br>
<br>
But then, I am just a n00bie. <p><a href="http://eq.castersrealm.com/players/view_profile.asp?Id=24077">Syui Chan</a> 54 Disciple - Ayonae Ro</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#383838><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub42.ezboard.com/ujzonn.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Jzonn</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Elite Poster</span><br> <font color=#ff0000>(2/23/01 12:41:46 am)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: A no brainer...</span><hr size=1> *gasp*  There <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i> must</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--> something wrong with that. <p><B><FONT FACE="Verdana" SIZE=2 COLOR="#3A6EA5">Jzonn Stormwolf &lt;Final Destiny&gt;</B></FONT><BR>
<I><FONT FACE="Verdana" SIZE=2 COLOR="#cfcfcf">Ranger of Karana</I></FONT></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#383838><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub42.ezboard.com/ubamdarcn.showPublicProfile?language=EN>BamdarCN</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>New to the block</span><br> <font color=#ff0000>(2/23/01 1:58:26 am)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: A no brainer...</span><hr size=1> The problem with that is you double the mana spent in the group (or more i think) per CH.  CoH is 500mana + a reagant I think?  That mana could be better spent elsewhere.  I didn't notice that big of a problem with heal and clerics getting beat up the last 2 days.  But time will tell, perhaps it'll be worth it.  But, it seems like spending a lot of mana that's not totally necessary.  Maybe mem blur or root, since it stacks with snare now, would be a better and cheaper alternative. <p></p><i>Edited by: <A HREF=http://pub42.ezboard.com/ubamdarcn.showPublicProfile?language=EN>BamdarCN</A> at: 2/23/01 2:00:02 am<br></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#383838><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub42.ezboard.com/utremainbladesinger.showPublicProfile?language=EN>TremainBladesinger</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Regular Poster</span><br> <font color=#ff0000>(2/23/01 4:26:24 am)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: A no brainer...</span><hr size=1> Yeah there is something wrong with that <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  : first of there is a longer recast time on CoH than on CH, second this would require a mage in every group, or two actually since its a 12 sec cast time and a 15 sec recast time. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#383838><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub42.ezboard.com/uedeina.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Edeina</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Arch Board Mistress</span><br> <font color=#ff0000>(2/23/01 6:08:04 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: A no brainer...</span><hr size=1> While this isn't a fix-it-all that could be used on a regular basis because of manacost, time, and that pesky reagent, it might still be a very valid better-then-nothing soultion in some speciffic raid situation. <p>Love, Edeina<br>
Highelf Conjurer of Erollisi<br>
Ayonae Ro Server<br>
<a href="http://Ayonae.Ro">Ayonae.Ro</a> Server Community Board</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#383838><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub42.ezboard.com/ujzonn.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Jzonn</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Elite Poster</span><br> <font color=#ff0000>(2/23/01 7:41:16 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: A no brainer...</span><hr size=1> Which is my point, Edeina.  Let's assume Verant is a bunch of idiots and decide they really, really like the new way.  Everyone in the group is responsible for managing the agro so the healers don't become mushy piles of goo.  The result?  Everyone learns new tactics and how to deal with the increased mana cost of 'doing business'.<br>
<br>
Now let's say Verant finally gets a clue three months later and reduces the agro (but not anywhere near it's original level) for healing.  Those lessons learned will be a huge benefit.  You may not need them as often, but you'll know about them for the times you do need them. <p><B><FONT FACE="Verdana" SIZE=2 COLOR="#3A6EA5">Jzonn Stormwolf &lt;Final Destiny&gt;</B></FONT><BR>
<I><FONT FACE="Verdana" SIZE=2 COLOR="#cfcfcf">Ranger of Karana</I></FONT></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#383838><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub42.ezboard.com/ukleg.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Kleg</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Regular Poster</span><br> <font color=#ff0000>(2/23/01 8:12:51 pm)</font><br>    <BR><img src=http://dynamic.gamespy.com/~cazic/cazic/ubb/uploads/Kleg.JPG WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: A no brainer...</span><hr size=1> I've noticed a little difference in the couple groups I've been in since the patch.  This is hardly the basis for a strong argument either way, however.<br>
<br>
Whether there is a problem or not, I fully expect VI to make some changes to taunt, hopefully with the next patch.  This issue was mentioned by most of the posters on the warrior class discussion thread.  Under the current system, and maybe since the last patch, a warrior has no trouble keeping a mob's attention.  Of course, that warrior needs some low delay weapons, and maybe one that procs, say a lamentation / jade mace and a blood point, and a dragon haste item.<br>
<br>
Unfortunately, most warriors aren't blessed with this setup.  I know my equipment is not ideal, although I'm working on the haste item.  If I could just convince Cati to slip me the CoF instead of randoming it on our next Naggy raid.....   <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START ;) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/wink.gif ALT=";)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br>
<br>
Anyway, since many warriors have less than ideal equipment, it's more of a challenge to keep the mob's attention.  Increasing the effectiveness of taunt may do nothing for the folks with the best stuff, but for the rest of us, it would be a much welcomed change. <p>---------------------------------------------------------<BR>
Kleg Omyleggo, Cute Halfling Warrior<BR>
Knights of the Night<BR>
